how fast a decisive CWLM can be.\nBasing on this, we devise and study a simple feedback scheme that attempts to\nkeep the qubit in the equal-weight superposition. The detector readings are\nused to decide in which state the qubit is and which correction rotation to\napply to bring it back to the superposition. We show how to optimize the\nfeedback parameters and move towards more efficient feedback schemes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Aug 2018 14:37:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-03"}
